In .NET 10 (starting with .NET 9 SR10+), `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated on Android because the underlying `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` flag was removed by Google.

The recommended replacement is to use **`KeyboardAutoManagerScroll`** (enabled by default) or handle it manually with **edge-to-edge / `WindowInsets`** awareness.

**Quick fix — ensure auto-scroll is enabled (default behavior):**

```csharp
// In MauiProgram.cs – this is ON by default in .NET 10,
// but if you disabled it previously, re-enable it:
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
    events.AddAndroid(android =>
    {
        android.OnCreate((activity, _) =>
        {
            Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect(activity);
        });
        android.OnDestroy(activity =>
        {
            Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect(activity);
        });
    });
});
```

**If auto-scroll doesn't suit your chat layout**, use the `Android WindowInsets` approach to add bottom padding dynamically:

```csharp
#if ANDROID
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

// In your page's handler or platform-specific code:
ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
    Platform.CurrentActivity!.Window!.DecorView, 
    new InsetsListener(yourBottomBar));

class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    private readonly View _target;
    public InsetsListener(View target) => _target = target;

    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        _target.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom);
        return insets;
    }
}
#endif
```

**TL;DR:** Remove any `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` calls and rely on the built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll`. For custom chat layouts, listen to IME `WindowInsets` and adjust padding/margin on your input bar accordingly.
